data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":246,"item_id":"msg_0ced2c8f7edf39b0006939d546ebf881959e6d38e5e260ca9b","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a Whistleblower Policy designed to maintain a safe and transparent working environment. This policy encourages employees to report any unethical or illegal activities they witness. Here's an overview:\n\n- **Applicability**: The policy applies to all Contoso Electronics employees, contractors, and third parties.\n- **Definition**: A whistleblower is someone who reports activities that are illegal or unethical.\n- **Reporting Procedures**: Employees can report concerns by:\n  1. Contacting Human Resources.\n  2. Emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com.\n  3. Calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212.\n\nEmployees can report anonymously if preferred. Reports should include details such as the time, date, people involved, and any evidence.\n\n- **Retaliation Prohibited**: Retaliation against whistleblowers is forbidden, and violators will face disciplinary action.\n- **Confidentiality**: The identity of the whistleblower will be kept confidential as permitted by law.\n- **Investigation**: All reported incidents will be investigated promptly and thoroughly.\n\nThe policy aims to foster ethical behavior and a transparent working environment.","logprobs":[]}

